Factory workers on strike knocked <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Poland</ENAMEX> 's <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Communist</ENAMEX> bosses off balance <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">last year</ENAMEX> ; <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">this year</ENAMEX> , it was the farmers who brought them down .
In <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">June</ENAMEX> , farmers held onto meat , milk and grain , waiting for <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">July</ENAMEX> 's usual state - directed price rises .
The <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Communists</ENAMEX> froze prices instead .
The farmers ran a boycott , and meat disappeared from the shops .
On <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">Aug. 1</ENAMEX> , the state tore up its controls , and food prices leaped .
